NUMBER 12
NAME Library, auditorium
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tiered stone circles rise from a central portion of floor towards a domed
ceiling with a magnificent painting of the Gods of Light watching over
the city of Fayd. Comfortable benches have been placed upon each tier to
allow the listener as much comfort as possible. An ornate wooden podium
sits in the center of the room, placed so as to allow the orator's voice
to carry to the furthest reaches of the room. A metal stairway,
unobtrusive in its placement, leads back down to the library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1226 ADJ1=192 VAL2=344
ITEM 1 479 ADJ1=534 ADJ2=355
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
On the front of the podium is the seal of the Lorekeepers, a golden
quill poised above a white parchment upon a field of blue.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The acoustics seem excellent in here.
ENDIF
