NUMBER 14
NAME Crafter Hall, Foyer
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The large foyer is a brightly lit room, immense windows set into arches that
curve up to a peak above you while dozen of torches sit in sconces, lit during
heavy weather and at night. A small table is set along the west wall, a large
scroll resting upon it and there is a large tapestry that takes up the entire
eastern wall. There is a door in the northeast corner through which merchants
can be seen haggling over materials of all shapes, colors, and sizes. At the
northwest corner of the room is a large arch leading into the hall's work area.
*DESCRIPTION_END
