; Heavy Silk Tapestry
ITEM 5 250 ADJ1=156 ADJ2=291
EXTEND 5 hanging from floor to ceiling on the west wall
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The immense silk tapestry must have been woven in sections for no loom could
ever hold it. Covering every inch of the tapestry are scenes of life in Fayd.
Starting during the demon wars in the upper left corner it progresses through
the history of Fayd, showing embattled streets in one scene, a large peaceful
wedding in the next, a unicorn sitting upon Hero's Hill in the next. The
colors of the threads are vibrant and the tapestry seems to come alive as
each scene melds into the next. The craftsmanship in this single tapestry is
the most detailed of any you have ever seen and most likely ever will see.
*DESCRIPTION_END
