NUMBER 20
NAME Library, history & misc.
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The icons of history can be found placed strategically throughout this
austere chamber. Weapons and armor hang alongside paintings showing
the glories of Fayd's, and Andor's, past. The books and scrolls
themselves reflect the passage of time, many of them looking as if
they were one page turn from falling apart. Wooden tables with cushioned
chairs offers places for the inquisitive to study in comfort. A black
arch leads out to the central chamber of the Library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=25 VAL2=344
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFSAY God_Wars
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper aids you in finding the appropriate information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The God Wars refers to the time when the powerful being named Siryx cast the Gods from the heavens down onto the plane of mortals in an attempt to usurp all of their power. Siryx was nearly successful in his plans but the Avatars, the mortal forms the Gods took, rallied together the adventurers of Fayd and sent them forth on quests to defeat the usurper. The epic journeys took the adventurers into alternate planes, into the body of a creature and, finally, into the stars themselves.
  ECHO PLAYER In the climactic battle the adventurers of Fayd crashed their starship, piloted by Endir, a mechanoid, into the ship being flown by Siryx. As the ships were wracked by explosions and flames, Ferumbras Firehand, Guildmaster of the Silver Arcana, was able weave magics around Siryx, binding him into place. With no escape possible Siryx was caught in the final explosion that destroyed both ships.
ENDIF
IFSAY Time_of_Tears
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper brings you some tomes to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER When Siryx returned for the second time to Andor he was driven by madness and a lust for vengeance. He sought to destroy Andor and the Gods as revenge for his first failure. He succeeded in destroying Kaliban, the God of Poverty and Humility, and fashioned a Black Mountain that touched the very molten core of Andor itself. As the world was shaking apart the adventurers of Fayd rallied together and stormed the Black Mountain, fighting their way to the top past the demonic creatures called by..
  ECHO PLAYER ...Siryx. Cornering Siryx in his chamber the assembled adventurers watched as Korazon, a Knight of Amilor, drove the Godslayer sword into Siryx' body, ending his threat to the universe for all eternity.
ENDIF
IFSAY Battle_of_Fayd
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER In the summer of 1013 the dreaded Broodlord, a Ravager of immense power, gathered his armies of Ravagers, Nightsteeds and Mountain Barbarians and descended upon Fayd, seeking its destruction. The battle raged for days, and time and again the determination of Fayd's defenders was tested. The armies of the Broodlord assaulted Fayd from every direction and were thrown back time and time again. Generals Joqain, Dagmar and Rune skillfully  moved their troops about...
  ECHO PLAYER ...sending them where they were most needed. Duke Moonpie and Duchess Camorra held the front gates of Fayd, nearly singlehandedly, as wave after wave of darkness crashed against them. King Frederick was always in the thick of the fighting, giving his citizens a beacon of hope in the turmoil. The climax of the battle took place in the Bazaar were the diminished band of defenders fought with such ferocity and determination that...
  ECHO PLAYER ...the forces of evil finally gave up, their losses too much to bear.
ENDIF
IFSAY Time_of_the_Bloodmoon
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper assists you in finding the information you seek...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER In the years 1016 and 1017 Fayd was plagued by a scourge of creatures that mimicked the ability of Vampires. These creatures were led by an alien being named Krangvak. Under Krangvak were three of his earliest victims, known as the Triad. The Triad were Krangvak's field generals, but Faydian adventurers defeated their plans to make Andor a feeding ground for the alien bloodsuckers at every turn.
  ECHO PLAYER Finally, the adventurers of Fayd travelled to the home planet of Krangvak and there, in an epic battle that last for nearly half a day, were able to defeat the menace, ending the threat he posed to Andor.
ENDIF
IFSAY Sunstrike
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper brings out some scrolls for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Sunstrike is the name for the magical sword wielded by Orlin Thinvar. It is the weapon that Orlin carried when he fought Malthesia.
ENDIF
IFSAY index
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper informs you that the following items can be referenced at this time...
  ECHO PLAYER ...SUNSTRIKE
  ECHO PLAYER ...TIME OF THE BLOODMOON
  ECHO PLAYER ...BATTLE OF FAYD
  ECHO PLAYER ...TIME OF TEARS
  ECHO PLAYER ...GOD WARS
ENDIF
