NUMBER 21
NAME Merchant's Hall
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The long room is dominated by the three large counters which stand along the
eastern and northern walls. Behind the first counter you can see roll upon
roll of cloth, large animal hides, and bushels of fine cotton. Many barrels of
various liquids stand next to stacks of metal rods behind the second counter,
and the third counter is covered with bottles, vials, flasks, and other gear
most often used by alchemists and wizards. A door leads back to the foyer.
*DESCRIPTION_END
