NUMBER 36
NAME Library, archives
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A musty, rectangular chamber that stretches nearly out of sight into the
dimly lit corners. Large wooden crates, mostly closed, are stacked atop
each other, in some cases, precariously, casting long shadows across the
slightly damp stone floor. Numerous young Lorekeepers scurry from crate
to crate, opening them to catalog the tomes and items they hold. A metal
stairway leads back up to the library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 81 ADJ1=192 VAL2=344
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFVERB SEARCH -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 < 3
    ECHO PLAYER You wouldn't know where to begin, never having had much training in the research required to unearth anything of interest here.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gets a slightly glazed look in %h eyes as %s makes a minor search of some nearby crates.
  ENDIF
   IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
     ECHO PLAYER You pore through some crates with a practiced eye, but don't manage to find anything of interest...today.
     ECHO OTHERS %N searches through some crates with a practiced scholar's eye.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
