NUMBER 37
NAME Library, info on Races
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Long wooden tables, with comfortable oak chairs placed around them, are
surrounded by shelves containing numerous texts on the races that populate
the world of Andor. Here and there on the shelves can be seen such
esoteric items as a sharkhor fin, an ursine pelt and a worm tongue. All
such items are, of course, contained within glass display cases.
A gold arch leads back out into the central hall of the Library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=147 VAL2=344
ITEM 1 86 ADJ1=216
ITEM 2 91 ADJ1=355
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFSAY Ephemeral
  ECHO PLAYER A courteous young Lorekeeper finds some books for you and sets them down on the table. You begin to read...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The ephemeral people are beings made of energy, magic, and soul. They have been viewed by many with suspicion and mistrust due to their differing appearance from most of the sentient life on Andor. The truth is they are a passionate people in a quiet way. They are lovers of knowledge of all sorts, from history and healing, to the arcane and unusual. They, for the most part, strive to maintain peace and tranquillity among themselves and with others.
  IFVAR SKILL32 => 5
    ECHO PLAYER After deciding to search for some more information on your own, using your research skills, you manage to find...
    ECHO PLAYER %c
    ECHO PLAYER They are also a people of rituals of the mind and magic. The nature of their minds and bodies allows them join into one group mind allowing them to accomplish things they cannot do alone. It is rumored that they are able to open gates for traveling the worlds, create beautiful works of art...that seem to blend with nature, and even look into the stream of time.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY Human
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding some books. You garner the following...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Human race is the most populous on Andor, though there are many different strains and cultures spread out across the world. Their history dates back to before the Cataclysm when they were purported to be the only race that could be found on Andor.
ENDIF
IFSAY Aelfen
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding some books. You garner the following...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Aelfen are beings closely attuned to nature and its inhabitants. While sharing many physical traits of humans Aelfen are set apart by their pointed ears, beautiful faces and their tall, lithe physiques. Rumors have it that many Aelfen live together in enclosed communities, shut off from the rest of the world, where they strive to heal the damage to nature caused by the Cataclysm.
ENDIF
IFSAY Nihvaenth
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper finds an ancient, weathered scroll and places it on the table before you...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER "After the Rain of Fire had ended the world was shattered, and where before there only had been one race, there were many new and young ones. One of these were the Aelfen...
  ECHO PLAYER "A time of confusion it was, and it was a slow process by where the many races of the land gathered into their own enclaves. Apart from each other, each race sought understanding of their own race, before venturing forth to learn of the others."
  ECHO PLAYER "The Aelfen, serving some inner force, perhaps placed there by Shemri, sought refuge in the few places of the world where Nature still held sway. It was in one such place of refuge that the Council of Moon and Sun met to discuss the future."
  ECHO PLAYER "From that meeting, which lasted for seven years, it was agreed that the Aelfen would become Nature's Protectors, and endeavor to nurture  its beauty, for, without it, Andor would surely die."
  ECHO PLAYER "Thus, the Aelfen travelled across the breadth of Andor, settling in communities such as Aniela, and began their task. For many years the Aelfen bent their collective will to their task, for it required single-minded concentration."
  ECHO PLAYER "But, as time passed, many of the Aelfen left these communities, an urge to see the world upon them. They left the communities with the blessings of their kin."
  ECHO PLAYER "These wandering Aelfen became known as Nihvaenth, or Wild Ones, and over the years there were many more  that wandered into the greater world. Communities, such as Aniela, became smaller, for, once left, the memories of these communities faded from the minds and memories of the Wild Ones, for such is the magic of these places."
ENDIF
IFSAY Mardhrel
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding the proper information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER "The Mardhrel, or Harvesters of Pain, are a blot upon the history of Aelfen. As is the case with all peoples, there will be some who resort to evil, or twisted, practices."
  ECHO PLAYER "Many years ago, a brilliant Pathwalker, named Galvaen began to delve into alternative methods of bringing Nature to its full glory. What he discovered was horrifying. He theorized that all things in nature passed through 'stages'...."
  ECHO PLAYER "As a pupae becomes the beautiful butterfly, so did Galvaen think that he could force the other aspects of nature to progress  to their final stages. But, he wanted it to happen quickly, and thus decided that he needed some sort of 'shock' to force things along."
  ECHO PLAYER "To achieve what he desired he began to inflict pain upon the trees, flowers and animals of Nature, hoping that the shock would carry them on to the next stage. Galvaen gained many followers, and they practiced their rites for many years."
  ECHO PLAYER "In time they were found out, and the other Aelfen were horrified by these practices. Galvaen and his followers were cast out by the other Aelfen, forced into warrens beneath the ground."
  ECHO PLAYER "There the Mardhrel still live, carrying out their heinous experiments.."
ENDIF
IFSAY Highlander
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings over some reading material while muttering, "If I catch Garin and Korazon carving each others names into the tables again, I'll...". You shut the Lorekeeper from your mind and peruse the texts...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER A race of stout beings who call the mountains their home. While shorter than the average human Highlanders are extremely strong and hardy. Their affinity for stone and gems leads them to have certain abilities when dealing with the materials, such as being able to mold gems and hide in rocky terrain.
ENDIF
IFSAY Murg
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper scratched his head, pondering, then manages to find some information for you...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER A fierce warrior-like race that makes their home in the mountains the Murgs are known for their ability to call upon a battle frenzy when in need. Their short, muscular bodies are well-suited for climbing and battle, but are somewhat lacking in the 'finer' skills.
ENDIF
IFSAY Drakin
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings some tomes over for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Also known as Dragonmen due to their physical appearance, upright humanoids but with scales, wings, claws and razor-sharp teeth, the Drakin are one of Andor's most mysterious races. They have developed their own set of beliefs, a code which espouses neutrality in all matters, they worship ancestor spirits rather than the Gods and they have developed their own unique combat styles which most effectively uses the various weapons crafted for it.
ENDIF
IFSAY Wolfling
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings some tomes over for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The children of Shemri, created to guard her forests from the depradations of foul creatures of darkness, especially werewolves whom they consider mortal enemies, are human appearing shapeshifters who can take on the form of a wolf. Noble and proud the Wolflings often turn from civilization to return to the woods they call home and the tribes they consider family.
ENDIF
IFSAY Mechanoid
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings some tomes over for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The youngest race on Andor, less than 400 years old, the Mechanoids were created from the merging of Ephemerals with robotic bodies during the Technomancy Wars. Able to turn their emotions off at will the Mechanoid is often seen as a coldly analytical being. They are renowned for their knowledge of technology, though the arts of magic are not available to them, due to their total lack of affinity for the flows of power.
ENDIF
IFSAY Vampire
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper gulps but brings over some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Not much is known of these secretive beings except for that they are strikingly similar to most humanoids, except for paler skin and, often, a slight rasp to their voice. Rumors and tales of Vampires are countless, though many seem to mention an aversion to the light of the sun, a taste for blood and the ability to transform into other forms.
ENDIF
IFSAY Kvantar
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper points out some books to you...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Living in a blackened copse of trees to the southeast of Fayd the Kvantar mutated humanoids changed into their horrid forms by some power granted them by their 'God' a large chunk of glowing red stone found inside a large tree in the cente of the woods. Their former leader, Maelmordha, was slain through the heroic actions of the Foresters Guild.
ENDIF
IFSAY Goblin
  ECHO PLAYER With the aid of a Lorekeeper you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Short, ugly, squat creatures living in the hills to the north of Fayd the goblins are known for their brutality. Often travelling in packs, for they are also fairly cowardly, they will set upon travellers, seeking to kill and plunder. Their society seems to be tribal based, with the strongest ruling the weak.
ENDIF
IFSAY Sharkhor
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Evil denizens of the Inner Sea the Sharkhor can often be seen roving the shores seeking to kill 'air breathers'. Physically they appear as upright sharks with the most distinguishing characteristic being the lifeless black eyes that seem to echo their malice towards the surface world. Rumors have it that they reside in an underwater city named Ryaleh in which their god, Calumra, also sleeps awaiting the day when it will awaken and lead the Sharkhor in a war against the surface world.
ENDIF
IFSAY Werewolf
  ECHO PLAYER A young Lorekeeper points you in the right direction...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Humanoids afflicted with the taint of darkness, the Werewolves are creatures of evil who appear as deadly wolves and seek to destroy all that is beautiful in nature.
ENDIF
IFSAY index
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper informs you that the following subjects can be referenced at this time...
  ECHO PLAYER ...HUMAN
  ECHO PLAYER ...AELFEN
  ECHO PLAYER ....--Nihvaenth
