NUMBER 38
NAME Library, people & places
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Paintings and sculptures of famous personages are tastefully placed on the
walls and between the shelves in this room. Comfortable reading chairs, each
with their own magical light hovering above them, are placed amongst the
shelves, offering the seeker of knowledge privacy if they so desire. A
silver arch leads back out to the central hall of the Library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=292 VAL2=344
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFSAY Siryx
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper shudders but brings you some information....
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Siryx, a powerful member of the mysterious organization known only as the Fold, has twice visited Andor and caused momentous events to unfold. The first time he brought the very Gods down from the heavens, forcing them to walk in mortal forms, in an attempt to become the one supreme God. His plans were foiled by adventurers from Fayd in a series of epic quests culminating in them crashing their starship into his. This time was known as the God Wars.
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The second time Siryx again attempted to usurp the Gods power. He crafted a Godslayer sword and with it succeeded in killing Kaliban, the God of Poverty and Humility. Only the bravery of the adventurers of Fayd stopped him again, as they battled their way up the Black Mountain and there cornered Siryx until Korazon could strike the final blow with the Godslayer sword. This time was known as the Time of Tears.
ENDIF
IFSAY Malthesia
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Malthesia is the most infamous necromancer on Andor. His power and knowledge are not surpassed by many and, in the past, he has attempted to conquer Fayd as a first step towards taking over all of Andor. His keep still remains to the northwest of Fayd, sitting there, brooding like a monument to darkness.
ENDIF
IFSAY Orlin
  ECHO PLAYER A lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Orlin Thinvar is renowned for defeating Malthesia with the aid of the sword, Sunstrike, ending the Necromancer's attempt to conquer Fayd. Though Orlin died in that final battle he is immortalized as one of the Heroes of Fayd with a statue on Heroes Hill.
ENDIF
IFSAY Rarg
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper finds some books for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER During the great fire that swept through Fayd nearly 300 years ago, Rarg Windrunner, a young wolfling male, showed exemplary heroism while saving many lives. Leaping time and time again into burning buildings to save lives, until, finally he succumbed while saving a human woman and child. For his deeds that day Rarg was honored with a place on top of Heroes Hill.
ENDIF
IFSAY Tilvaen
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper hands you an old scroll with some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER In the 600's a deadly plague swept through Fayd, killing all it touched. If it had not been for the efforts of Tilvaen Treegrower, an aelfen Forester, Fayd may have perished. Tilvaen journeyed far into the frozen north where after many adventures managed to discover a cure for the plague. He brought this back to Fayd and managed to halt the virus. Unfortunately, Tilvaen did not have enough antidote left to cure himself and, thus, ventured back into the Frozen Wastes of the north.
  ECHO PLAYER Tilvaen was never heard from him again, but his heroism was rewarded with a statue atop Heroes Hill.
ENDIF
IFSAY Strom
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper says, "I remember Strom O'Berin", as he finds some information for you...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER During the time of the God Wars there were many acts of bravery and heroism, but none exmplified the sacrifice and courage durig that time as much as Strom O'Berin. An aelfen Priest of Shemri, Strom ventured into danger time and time again to heal wounds and save lives during the battles against Siryx. For his selfless heroism Strom was rewarded with a statue atop Heroes Hill.
ENDIF
IFSAY Solaria
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Princess Solaria Kentaurus was renowned for her never ending struggle against darkness, vampires in particular. She was the Champion of Rorin, his most famous knight, and carried armor and weapons forged by the God for her. She met her end in battle against undead armies that sought to overrun the city she loved. While she lived she was the living embodiment of valor, courage and determination, for these qualities and more she is honored with a statue atop Heroes Hill.
ENDIF
IFSAY Broodlord
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings the information you requested...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Broodlord was a powerful Ravager who gathered together an army of darkness to attack Fayd in the Summer of 1013. He had originally come to Andor as part of a group of Ravagers called from their dimension by a being called the Mistmaster.
ENDIF
IFSAY Grymwood
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings the information you requested...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Located to the west of Fayd, past the river Eltinmar, is the demesne of the Grymwood Forest. Home to all manner of fell creatures, including Vashaska and her Banshees in the Matriarch Tree, Werewolves, Ettins, Boars, Trolls and Imps. The Grymwood can also be a place of startling beauty as it is a place where the power of nature runs strong. A reputed sage, one Menelian, also makes his home in the Grymwood. It is said that the entrance to his cottage is magically hidden, only...
  ECHO PLAYER ...appearing at certain times throughout the day.
ENDIF
IFSAY Heroes_Hill
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper bring out some tomes for you to peruse...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Just southeast of the gates leading into Fayd lies Heroes Hill. Upon the top of the hill are the statues of Fayd's greatest heroes, memorialized there forever.
ENDIF
IFSAY Shartan
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper helps you find the information you seek...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Teeth of Shartan is a vast mountain range to the north of Fayd. Named for a son of Shemri, the Goddess, the jagged peaks and valleys are home for many creatures both good and bad. Giants and Ogres roam the higher peaks while Ursines and Aeyskroks can be found in the vales. It is rumored that the entrance to the ruined academy of learning called Mirdaal lies somewhere in the Shartans.
ENDIF
IFSAY Deep_Realms
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings out some parchments for your reading pleasure...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER A vast network of natural caverns and passageways combine to form the Deep Realms. Within its dark depths can be found many creatures and many mysteries. The beauty of the Crystal Caverns is said to be breathtaking and amongst the other places to visit are Kragenholm, the town of the Deeplanders and the Gurkan Village. It is said that through the Deep Realms one can find paths that lead to the realm of the Sharkhor and also to alternate planes.
  ECHO PLAYER The entrance to the Deep Realms is well hidden, but some say that Menelian the Sage of the Grymwood can aid the intrepid adventurer.
ENDIF
IFSAY index
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper informs you that the following subjects can be found at this time...
  ECHO PLAYER ...SIRYX
  ECHO PLAYER ...MALTHESIA
  ECHO PLAYER ...ORLIN
  ECHO PLAYER ...TILVAEN
  ECHO PLAYER ...RARG
  ECHO PLAYER ...STROM
  ECHO PLAYER ...SOLARIA
  ECHO PLAYER ...BROODLORD
  ECHO PLAYER ...GRYMWOOD
  ECHO PLAYER ...HEROES HILL
  ECHO PLAYER ...SHARTAN
  ECHO PLAYER ...DEEP REALMS
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 39
NAME Library, gods & myths
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Symbols of the Gods of Light can be found in all corners of this room,
engraved into the walls, stitched into the plush rugs upon the floor and
embossed upon the tomes that line the shelves. The presence of the deities
is nearly overwhelming, and reverential, silent movements of the Lorekeepers
on duty here echo the feeling. A white arch leads back out to the main
chamber of the Library.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=347 VAL2=344
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

IFSAY Shemri
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper nods slightly to you and then brings you some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Goddess of Life, Nature and Beauty, Shemri appears as a beautiful young woman cloaked in a brilliant white light. She is known for her compassion and kindness, but can also be temperemental and vengeful when her ire is raised. She is the wife of Amilor and her symbol is a golden great oak inlaid onto a silver disk.
ENDIF
IFSAY Amilor
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper helps you find some information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Amilor, Lord of the Deep, has as his domain the the oceans, the sea and the weather. He is depicted as a powerful and handsome man, often within a crashing wave of water. His symbol is a silver wave within a golden circle.
ENDIF
IFSAY Rorin
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper brings some tomes over to you...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Rorin, the Lord of Light, rules over the sun and its rays. He is an aggressive, war-like god and hates the darkness of undead with a passion. His symbol is that of a golden eight-rayed sun.
ENDIF
IFSAY Kaliban
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper points out the shelf holding the information you seek...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Kaliban, the former God of Poverty and Humility, met his end at the hands of Siryx during the Time of Tears. Kaliban was a gentle and helpful god, his followers always seeking to aid the less fortunate. When he passed on a star ascended into the night sky, a memorial to this gentle God.
ENDIF
IFSAY Devourer
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper cringes and looks around fearfully, but finally points you to a darkened corner of the room...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Devourer is the God of Darkness and Death. His name, Dahkahn, is not spoken aloud for fear of gaining his attention. The rites his followers use in worship of him are heinous and often involve living sacrifices. His symbol is unknown, but thought to be something dark and evil.
ENDIF
IFSAY Elorna
  ECHO PLAYER The Lorekeeper brings over a book embossed with the symbol of a silver moon...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Elorna, the Lady of the Silvery Light, is the beautiful Goddess of the Moon and Stars. Her tenets are those of peace and compassion, embodied in the comfort those who worship her gain. Elorna is Rorin's sister and often tempers her brothers aggressiveness.
ENDIF
IFSAY Ordanin
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper helps you find the appropriate information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Ordanin, the Keeper of the Scales, is the God of Justice. His tenets are those of swift and sure justice for those condemned of crimes. He is the God awakened to take Kaliban's place.
ENDIF
IFSAY Yarin
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper points out the appropriate shelf to look upon...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Yarin, the Goddess of Knowledge, is identified with the pursuit of wisdom and knowledge. Her followers believe in neutrality as a tenet, for knowledge is neither light nor dark.
ENDIF
IFSAY Calumra
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper leads you over to a less used portion of the room...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Calumra is the evil deity of the Sharkhor. It is represented as a squid of terrifying size and is always sleeping, dreaming its dreams of taking the surface world by conquest.
ENDIF
IFSAY Ahkr
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Ahkr, the Wandering God, is a deity of the Desert Nomads far to east, he is known as the God of Faith, Chaos and Impatience, and is also referred to as the Patron of Djinn. He is depicted as a dark, brooding figure atop a black stallion. [Submitted by Queen Zorha.]
ENDIF
IFSAY index
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper informs you that the following names can be referenced...
  ECHO PLAYER ...SHEMRI
  ECHO PLAYER ...AMILOR
  ECHO PLAYER ...RORIN
  ECHO PLAYER ...DEVOURER
  ECHO PLAYER ...KALIBAN
  ECHO PLAYER ...ORDANIN
  ECHO PLAYER ...YARIN
  ECHO PLAYER ...CALUMRA
  ECHO PLAYER ...AHKR
  ECHO PLAYER ...DRAKIN RELIGION
  ECHO PLAYER     --Great Hall
ENDIF
IFSAY drakin_religion
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding information...
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER Drakin modes of worship differ from clan to clan but one factor remains constant, the Drakin do not worship the Gods of Andor. They show respect for the Gods, but choose, rather, to worship the Spirits of their Ancestors. Worship is a bit of a misnomer though, as the Drakin do not actually pray, offer sacrifices, etc. to their Ancestors, rather they Revere and Honor those Ancestors who have gained entry into the Great Hall.
  ECHO PLAYER One example of the 'worship' the Drakins practice is a clan where items once held by the Ancestor Spirits are passed down from generation to generation. Ornamental tattoos are also worn by the Drakins of this clan, the tattoos often depicting scenes from the life of the Ancestor Spirit. [Submitted by Fafnir Deathwing.]
ENDIF
IFSAY great_hall
  ECHO PLAYER A Lorekeeper assists you in finding some information..
  ECHO PLAYER %c
  ECHO PLAYER The Great Hall is an alternate plane, consisting entirely of a long stone hallway stretching out endlessly, where the spirits of Drakins go, after death, if they have led an honorable life.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 96
NAME Eternity, Inc., Waiting Room
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
IFENTRY -1
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 180
  EQUAL BODYPOINTS 1
  POSITION LAY
  IFVAR ORG = 20
    ECHO PLAYER You find yourself snatched from the room and whisked away down a long tunnel of strobing lights.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You see a brief view of chanting priests in an underground temple.  Then you are wisked away.
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER You find yourself slammed on a flat wooden floor.
    MOVE 674
    POSITION LAY
    AFFECT 674
    ECHO OTHERS %N appears out of a swirling vortex and crashes to the floor.
    ECHO PLAYER You feel extremely weak.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You feel extremely weak.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in a featureless room where clients of Eternity Inc. may rest once their lives are restored. A thoughtful employee has posted a sign here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 220
IFPREVERB OUT -1
  ECHO PLAYER As you leave, a helpful employee informs you that due to tens of thousands of deaths, the wear and tear on the machinery has mandated some changes in how body recovery is handled.
ENDIF
