NUMBER 317
NAME Jeweler Workshop
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
FORGE
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This segment of the immense workroom is outfitted with all manner of fine tools
designed especially for the jeweler's craft. The center of the room is taken up
by a multi-station forge which is broken into small compartments to melt down
only small quantities of metal at a time. The two long workbenches that form
the border of this area meet at the base of the spiral stairs in the northeast
corner. One the workbenches is outfitted with equipment to aid fletchers in
the making of arrows here as well. An archway leads back to the foyer and there
is a passage leading off to the southwest, possibly passing behind the building
housing the Physician's Guild.
*DESCRIPTION_END
