NUMBER 323
NAME Rake Hall
DEEPCAVE
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This smoky room is the scene of quite an intense party. A large number of
foppish individuals are engaged in every form entertainment imaginable. Seated
around a circular oak table are five men engaged in what appears to be a
serious card game. If the piles of coins in front of the players are any
indication they have been here for a while. A drunk minstrel provides debauched
entertainment to a mixed group on a couch. The decor of the room itself is
exquisite, mahogany paneled walls and plush royal red carpeting. The clinking
of the crystal and china being used by the revellers also adds to the
impression of wealth.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 322
EXIT N 324
ITEM 9 693 ADJ1=10

;
NUMBER 324
NAME Rake Hall, Training
DEEPCAVE
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
In marked contrast to the festivities to the south, this room is filled with
erious minded individuals engaging in training. While dressed as gaudily as
the rest of the people in the house, the intensity shown by the occupants of
this room gives one pause to wonder if the dapper show is a clever facade. The
training itself seems to consist of "rogue" skills. In one corner of the room
trainees attempt to sneak up on their instructors while wearing bells tied to
their legs and arms. In another section of the large chamber, students try to
lift a pouch from the pocket of their instructor without jingling any of the
bells placed in the same pocket as the pouch. The central area of the chamber
is the scene of some energetic fencing duels.
*DESCRIPTION_END
