*DESCRIPTION_START
The pipes from the outside corridors all enter this room and soon become lost in what looks like a maze of oddly angled and joined pipes. Interspersed amongst the jumble are some square metal boxes that have many dials, switches, and buttons upon them. The room is very quiet, except for the occasional scraping noise. Cobwebs and rust are prevalent amongst the gnarled mass of metal on the floor. A door leads out to the corridors.
*DESCRIPTION_END
