NUMBER 344
NAME Library
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
An eternally lit bronze brazier casts its light across the breadth of
a polished marble chamber. The brazier sits in the center of an intricate
mosaic depicting the symbol of the Lorekeepers of Fayd, a golden quill
suspended over a curling white parchment. Tall, fluted pillars of white
marble circle the chamber, their polished white marble exteriors glistening
softly with reflected light. Decorative arches, engraved with the symbols
of learning and knowledge lead further into the depths of the library. A
spiral metal stairway rises from floor to ceiling allowing movement in both
the up and down direction. Prominently displayed behind an oaken desk is a
large gold sign.
*DESCRIPTION_END
